news.title: China Evergrande's CEO, CFO step down after probe into property services unit
news.para: The indebted company was investigating how deposits worth 13.4 billion yuan ($1.99 billion) belonging to the unit, Evergrande Property Services, were used as collateral for pledge guarantees and seized by banks.

news.title: Schindler cuts revenue guidance for 2022 on China slowdown
news.para: CEO Silvio Napoli said on a conference call that China's market could contract by 15% to 30% this year. China accounted for around 18% of Schindler's sales last year.

news.title: Pune: Seven housing societies fined for not processing waste at source
news.para: As per the guidelines, housing societies or commercial establishments generating more than 100kg of garbage, categorized as bulk waste generators, should process the wet waste on their premises.

news.title: Goa: Now, TCP to create zoning plans for areas not under ODPs
news.para: With the passing of the Goa Town and Country Planning (Amendment) Bill, 2022, the TCP will prepare a ‘zoning plan’ for ‘local planning areas’ to carry out development plans in panchayat and municipal areas which are not covered under outline development plans (ODPs).

news.title: Bengaluru: 94% land acquired for airport metro
news.para: The project entails 5-7 km of track-length from Central Silk Board to Kempegowda International Airport. Around 30 stations will be a part of this project, the cost of which is estimated to be Rs 14,788 crore.

news.title: Gurugram & Faridabad admins face tough challenge to remove encroachers from PLPA land
news.para: Officials said the process of issuing notices will begin from next week in both the districts. Forest department data shows most of this land is in Faridabad (850 acres).

news.title: Govt nod to proposal to exclude 'will' as mandatory document for availing PM-UDAY benefits: DDA
news.para: ​Around 1,500-2,000 applications are awaiting clearance under the scheme as currently a 'will' is a mandatory document to avail benefits of , the urban body said in a statement.

news.title: Penalty on officers who fail to prevent building violations: BBMP to HC
news.para: ​In an affidavit filed before the High Court by the civic agency's Chief Commissioner Tushar Giri Nath (IAS) on Friday, the details of the two new circulars dated July 6 and July 21 have been mentioned.

news.title: NDMC seeks structural audit report, building plans from owners within one month
news.para: ​The NDMC has issued a public notice to inform the owners and occupiers of buildings located in its area to submit structure safety audit and building plan in its department of Architecture and Environment.

news.title: If sealed building illegal, raze in 60 days: Ghaziabad development body
news.para: Enforcement of the process, they said, will help maintain proper documentation of any action by the authority and weed out corruption as some juniors tend to seal and de-seal properties on their own accord.

news.title: No survey yet, Noida circle rates likely to stay same this year
news.para: Suhas LY, district magistrate, said that the administration has not yet held a meeting over circle rate revision. “No decision has been taken on the issue. But the circle rate can be revised any time during the year. We can revise it as and when we want,” he said.

news.title: Noida authority to discuss evacuation plan of Supertech twin towers' demolition day
news.para: Senior officials of the developer Supertech, Edifice Engineering, the company that will carry out the demolition, the National Disaster Response Force (NDRF) and police will attend the meeting, which has been convened by the CEO of the Noida Authority.

news.title: Don't burden us with additional cost: Amrapali homebuyers in SC
news.para: According to the initial estimate submitted by NBCC, Rs 8,106 crore would be needed for the completion of 46,575 flats.

news.title: MahaRERA changes developer for incomplete project; also appoints ex-Babu to monitor
news.para: Pradeep Wandrekar, chairperson of Sadaphuli Cooperative housing society Ltd had filed two complaints, one against DSK Worldman projects ltd and one against DSK and Company under RERA alleging that the promoter of the project called DSK Sadaphuli.

news.title: HC directs Mumbai police commissioner to trace, arrest Orbit Ventures Developer's directors
news.para: Axis Finance had filed a contempt petition against Orbit Ventures Developers and their two directors, Rajen Dhruv and Hiren Dhruv who reside in Bandra (west) and Khar (West).
